                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72114/4237a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-09T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 9, 1918—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>154. Military Attaché, Berne, reports under date of December 5th<note n="8"
                        xml:id="d412fn8">Report not printed.</note> critical condition of 20,000
                    Russian officers now prisoners in Germany. Fear that if they returned to Russia
                    it would mean certain death. Department would like to know whether the matter
                    was being considered by the Supreme War Council and what action if any had been
                    taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
